import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='num_dependencies', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['num_dependencies'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['num_dependencies'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of dependencies?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='num_dependencies', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="source", y="num_dependencies", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What is the most common source in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['num_dependencies'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max value: {:.2f}'.format(data['num_dependencies'].max()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['target'] = data['target'].astype(str)
    target_counts = data['target'].value_counts()
    target_counts = target_counts[:10,]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
    sns.barplot(target_counts.index, target_counts.values, alpha=0.8)
    plt.title('What is the most common target in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Number of Occurrences', fontsize=12)
    plt.xlabel('Target', fontsize=12)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
